1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Bf4 Nc6 5. e3 e6 6. Nc3 Bd7 $2 {This is a passive move from Black. There is no concrete theory and White again has a choice between many moves.} (6... Bd6 7. Bxd6 Qxd6 8. Bd3 Nf6 (8... Nge7 9. Nf3 O-O 10. O-O e5 (10... f6 11. e4 $14) 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Be2 $14) 9. Nf3 $5 (9. f4 $14) 9... O-O 10. O-O e5 (10... b6 11. Rc1 Bb7 12. a3 Rac8 13. b4 $14) 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Be2 {Here is a sample line of how the play can develop in a position where Black has an isolated pawn on d5.} Be6 13. Nb5 Qb8 14. Nxe5 Qxe5 15. Qd4 (15. Nd4 $14) 15... Qxd4 16. Nxd4 Rac8 17. f3 Rc5 18. Rfc1 Rfc8 19. Rxc5 Rxc5 20. Kf2 Kf8 21. g4 Ke7 22. Bd3 h6 23. h4 a6 24. Ke2 Bd7 25. Kd2 Rc8 26. Rg1 $14) 7. Bd3 Bb4 {White shouldn't be afraid of Bxc3+ since it's not really a threat in these types of positions.} 8. Nf3 $5 Nf6 (8... Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 Na5 {Even if Black manages to take control over the c4-square, it's not a problem since White has plenty of resources in the position.} 10. O-O Rc8 11. Rc1 (11. Ne5 $16) 11... Nc4 12. Bxc4 Rxc4 13. Ne5 Rc8 14. Qg4 $16) 9. O-O O-O 10. Ne5 Bxc3 11. bxc3 h6 (11... Na5 {Black isn't able to play on both sides of the board, so now the Black's kingside will be under pressure. Additionally, it's difficult for Black to attack the c-pawn more than once with ...Rc8, so Rc1 will simply defend it if needed. The move 12.g4 is premature as White doesn't have a concrete target on the kingside, so White's next move is better.} 12. Bg5 {The absence of Black's light-squared bishop can be easily felt now.} Be8 13. Ng4 $18 (13. f4 $18 {This move is also possible, Intending Rf3.})) 12. Rb1 (12. c4 $16) 12... Na5 13. Qe2 Rc8 14. Rfc1 a6 15. g4 $1 {This is a great move, initiating an attack against Black's king and taking advantage of the hook on h6!} g5 (15... b5 16. g5 hxg5 17. Bxg5 Be8 18. Kh1 $18 {Rg1 is coming next with a likely checkmating attack.} (18. Ng4 $18)) (15... Ne8 16. h4 $16) 16. Bg3 b5 17. f3 $1 Kg7 18. h4 $16 Be8 (18... Nc4 19. Bxc4 dxc4 (19... bxc4 20. Rb7 $18) 20. e4 $18) 19. Kg2 Rg8 20. hxg5 hxg5 21. Qd2 Qe7 22. Rh1 Qa3 23. Rbc1 Kf8 24. Rh6 Ke7 25. e4 b4 26. c4 b3 27. exd5 Nxd5 28. Ra1 Ne3+ 29. Qxe3 Qb2+ 30. Be2 Qxa1 31. axb3 Qb2 32. d5 Qxb3 33. d6+ Kd8 34. Qd2 Rc5 35. d7 Rxe5 36. dxe8=Q+ Kxe8 37. Bxe5 Nxc4 38. Bxc4 Qxc4 39. Bf6 Qd5 40. Qxd5 exd5 41. Bc3 Rg6 42. Rxg6 fxg6 43. Bd2 Kd7 44. Kf2 Kc6 45. Ke3 Kc5 46. Kd3 1-0

