{[%evp 0,91,29,29,26,14,14,14,6,15,22,25,34,25,25,25,25,4,3,-7,-7,-8,-8,-7,8,10,29,9,119,112,112,128,131,92,92,135,142,153,153,10,64,-24,48,69,127,119,136,122,226,236,260,204,263,227,220,208,205,203,203,203,205,219,219,214,220,223,219,217,234,238,268,229,297,300,297,300,300,322,331,347,391,360,514,451,466,606,606,648,668,671,740,840,840,842] This game shows how White should handle the position when Black goes for the plan with ...b7-b6.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Be7 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bxf6 Bxf6 7. e3 O-O 8. Qd2 b6 {Obviously, Black is planning to develop his light-squared bishop via b7. The problem is that this is a slow approach that does not fit into the spirit of the position.} 9. O-O-O {The most natural follow-up.} ({Another interesting option would have been} 9. cxd5 $5 exd5 10. Bd3 Bb7 11. Rd1 Nd7 12. Bc2 $14 {when White retains a small advantage in a strategic type of game. Black's main problem is the passive light-squared bishop. Also, for the moment, it's not so simple to carry out the advance ...c7-c5.}) 9... Bb7 $2 {This is already a mistake because, after cxd5, the b7-bishop will remain passive.} ({A better option would have been} 9... dxc4 $5 10. Bxc4 Bb7 11. Qe2 Nd7 12. e4 $36 {Even though the computer gives only a small edge for White in this position, practically speaking, our play is a lot easier.}) 10. cxd5 {When you see a bishop on b7, this capture is always a logical reaction.} ({In my opinion, starting with} 10. h4 {would have been even more flexible.}) 10... exd5 11. h4 $16 {[%cal Gg2g4,Gg4g5] This is the point. Now, the advance g2-g4-g5 becomes a serious threat.} Qd7 ({In case of} 11... c5 {, instead of winning a pawn, it's better to keep attacking with} 12. g4 {If Black plays} cxd4 {I would play} 13. exd4 {[%cal Gg4g5] The reason for this recapture is that I would like to use the f6-bishop as a target.}) 12. Bd3 c5 13. Bb1 $3 {[%cal Gd2c2] Remember this typical attacking idea. White wants to follow with Qc2. The idea is that ...g7-g6 will always be met by h4-h5. Later on, White won the game.} Rc8 14. Qc2 Kf8 15. Qh7 Qd6 16. Bf5 Nd7 17. Ne5 Bc6 18. f4 Ke7 19. Bxd7 Bxd7 20. dxc5 Qxc5 21. Nxd7 Kxd7 22. Qe4 Qe7 23. Qa4+ Rc6 24. e4 Kc7 25. e5 Rc4 26. Qxc4+ dxc4 27. Nd5+ Kc6 28. Nxe7+ Bxe7 29. Rd4 b5 30. Rhd1 Rc8 31. Rd7 Rc7 32. Rxc7+ Kxc7 33. h5 Kc6 34. Kc2 a5 35. g4 Kc7 36. a4 bxa4 37. Kc3 a3 38. bxa3 Bxa3 39. Kxc4 Kc6 40. g5 Be7 41. g6 f6 42. Ra1 fxe5 43. fxe5 Bd8 44. Rf1 Bc7 45. Rf6+ gxf6 46. exf6 1-0

