{[%evp 0,67,36,27,27,4,4,4,46,23,8,26,11,-14,-4,-4,30,7,21,-9,4,26,24,11,19,27,1,26,26,11,55,53,60,73,74,74,88,97,97,100,115,108,131,141,200,152,144,154,155,133,190,187,260,302,302,156,156,173,179,176,176,176,239,247,334,409,409,372,377,331]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. cxd5 cxd4 5. Qxd4 Nc6 6. Qd1 exd5 7. Qxd5 Bd7 8. Nf3 Nf6 9. Qd1 Bc5 10. a3 Qe7 11. b4 {This move is OK, but I would prefer 11.Bg5 instead} Bb6 12. Bg5 Be6 13. e3 Rd8 14. Qc2 Bg4 15. Be2 O-O (15... Bxf3 {We are already familiar with the idea:} 16. gxf3 $18 (16. Bxf6 Qxf6 17. Bxf3 Ne5 18. Be2 O-O 19. O-O Rc8 20. Rac1 $18) 16... O-O 17. O-O Rfe8 18. Rfd1 $16) 16. O-O h6 17. Bh4 g5 18. Bg3 Nh5 19. Rad1 Nxg3 20. hxg3 Qf6 21. Nd5 Qg7 22. Nxb6 axb6 23. b5 {White is very solid and ends up with a healthy pawn up} Na5 24. Nd4 Rc8 25. Nc6 f5 26. Bxg4 fxg4 27. Qa2+ Kh8 28. Nxa5 bxa5 29. Qe6 Qf6 30. Qxg4 Rc2 31. Rd7 Rxf2 32. Rxf2 Qxf2+ 33. Kh2 Rf7 34. Rxb7 1-0

