1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. cxd5 cxd4 5. Qa4+ Bd7 6. Qxd4 exd5 7. Qxd5 {The Stockfish gives a big advantage for White, but things are far from easy} Nf6 8. Qd1 Bc5 9. Nf3 O-O 10. e3 Qe7 11. Be2 Nc6 12. O-O Ne5 13. Bd2 (13. Nxe5 {I loike a lot White's position after: is:} Qxe5 14. Bf3 Rad8 15. Qe2 Bc6 16. Bxc6 bxc6 17. Bd2 $16) 13... Rad8 14. Nd4 Nc6 15. Nf3 (15. Nxc6 $6 {We shouldn't allow Black's bishop to occupy the a8-h1 diagonal} Bxc6 16. Bf3 Bxf3 17. gxf3 Qd7 18. Be1 Qh3 $19) 15... Ne5 16. Qc2 b5 (16... Bc6 17. Nd4 {White can give the pawn back} (17. Rfd1 {the engines prefer White after:} Nxf3+ 18. Bxf3 Bxf3 19. gxf3 {[%cal Rc3e2]}) 17... Bxd4 18. exd4 Rxd4 19. Be3 $13) 17. a3 Bd6 18. Nd4 a6 19. Nf5 Bxf5 20. Qxf5 $16 Bxa3 21. Bc1 Bd6 22. Rxa6 b4 23. Nb5 Bb8 24. Nd4 Rd5 25. Qh3 Ne4 26. f4 Nd7 27. Nf5 Qc5 28. Rc6 Qa5 29. Ne7+ Kh8 30. Ra6 Qc5 31. Nxd5 Qxd5 32. Rd1 1-0

