1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nc6 {The Chigorin variation.} 3. cxd5 Qxd5 4. e3 {White is threatening to play Nc3 and d5 with tempo which would lead to a big advantage.} e5 {The only chance for Black to fight back, otherwise White gets a big advantage with simple moves.} 5. Nc3 Bb4 {This is Black's idea, pinning the knight on c3 and keeping the queen in the center.} 6. a3 (6. Nf3 exd4 7. exd4 {This position actually transposes to the Danish Gambit, but 6.a3 is a better option on move 6.}) 6... Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 {This opening is very risky and although it's true that Black scored some very nice victories, Black was always objectively much worse.} Nf6 (7... exd4 $6 8. cxd4 Nf6 9. Ne2 {The knight is heading to the c3-square in order to dislodge the queen from the d5-square.} O-O 10. Nc3 Qd6 11. Be2 {White has an advantage and stabilizes the position first by developing and castling, and only then looks for active plans, for example how to expand in the center properly.}) 8. c4 Qd6 9. d5 Ne7 10. a4 {Intending Ba3.} Nd7 (10... c5 {Black can play c5 sooner or later where usually White shouldn't capture en passant.} 11. Ne2 {The knight can go to g3 or c3 next.} O-O 12. Nc3 $16 {White has a strategically winning position with the space advantage and a strong protected passed pawn on d5, while Black's blockade is unhealthy with the queen standing in front of the pawn.}) 11. Ba3 Nc5 12. Nf3 (12. Ne2 {This is an improvement over 12.Nf3, intending Nc3 next.} O-O 13. Nc3 $16) 12... Ng6 13. Be2 O-O 14. O-O a5 15. Nd2 b6 16. Ne4 Qe7 17. Nxc5 bxc5 18. Rb1 Ba6 19. Qd2 e4 20. Rfc1 Ne5 21. Qd4 cxd4 22. Bxe7 d3 23. Bxf8 dxe2 24. Bc5 Nd3 25. Bd4 Nxc1 26. Rxc1 Bxc4 27. f3 Bxd5 28. Kf2 exf3 29. gxf3 Bb3 30. Ra1 Bd1 31. Bc3 f6 32. Ra2 c5 33. e4 c4 34. Rd2 Bxa4 35. Kxe2 Be8 36. Rd4 a4 37. Ke3 Bf7 38. Rd7 a3 39. Kd2 a2 40. Ba1 Rb8 41. Ra7 Rb1 42. Ra8+ Be8 43. Bc3 Kf7 44. Rxa2 Rh1 45. Ke3 Bd7 46. f4 Bc6 47. Ra7+ Kf8 48. Rc7 Ba4 49. Rxc4 Bb5 50. Rc8+ Kf7 51. Rc7+ Kf8 52. e5 fxe5 53. Bxe5 Rxh2 54. Bxg7+ Kg8 55. Be5 Rh3+ 56. Kd4 Bd3 57. Rg7+ Kf8 58. Kd5 Bf5 59. Ra7 Rd3+ 60. Bd4 h5 61. Ke5 h4 62. Bc5+ Kg8 63. Kxf5 Rd5+ 64. Kg6 Rxc5 65. Ra8+ Rc8 66. Rxc8# 1-0

