1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nc6 {If you play against a player which is well prepared in the Chigorin as Black, they will probably know the way to be only slightly worse.} 3. cxd5 Qxd5 4. e3 e5 5. Nc3 Bb4 6. a3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 Nf6 8. c4 Qd6 9. d5 Nb8 10. Ne2 O-O 11. Nc3 Bf5 12. Be2 Na6 (12... e4 {If Black plays e4, it gives up control of the d4-square, and White's dark-squared bishop will be very strong on the a1-h8 diagonal.}) 13. O-O Nc5 14. a4 a6 15. Ba3 e4 16. a5 Nfd7 17. Na4 b6 18. Rb1 Rfe8 19. axb6 cxb6 20. g4 Qg6 21. Kh1 Bxg4 22. Bxg4 Nxa4 23. Bxd7 Nc3 24. Qc2 Nxb1 25. Qxb1 Re5 26. Rg1 Qf6 27. Rg2 Rd8 28. Bc6 Qf3 29. Kg1 Rf5 30. Be7 Rb8 31. d6 Re5 32. Rg3 Qf5 33. d7 Rxe7 34. Qxb6 1-0

