1. c4 e6 2. Nc3 d5 3. d4 Bb4 4. a3 {This move and 4.e3 are trying to take advantage of the 3...Bb4 move.} Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 Nf6 (5... dxc4 {This capture doesn't work well for Black.} 6. e4 b5 7. a4 c6 8. Qg4 $14 {White has very good compensation for the pawn.}) 6. e3 {White's idea is to capture on d5 and play Bd3. Black can capture on c4 first, but Black will be a tempo down compared to a Nimzo-Indian where White usually spends a tempo with Bd3 first and then Bxc4.} c6 {Black plans to recapture on d5 with the c-pawn.} 7. a4 $5 {This is a good try from White to play for an advantage, although I prefer the move 7.cxd5. After 7.a4, White wants to continue with Ba3 next.} (7. cxd5 cxd5 8. c4 O-O 9. cxd5 exd5 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. Ne2 $14) 7... O-O 8. Ba3 Re8 9. Nf3 b6 $1 {This is Black's main idea in this 6...c6 system, a quick b6-Ba6 since Black's light-squared bishop is blocked within the pawn chain.} (9... Nbd7 {White has a choice between capturing on d5 or playing Bd3 first. Black has some difficulties in developing the bishop on c8.}) 10. cxd5 cxd5 11. Bb5 $1 {Again, this typical Bb5 idea in order to disturb the coordination between Black's pieces and not allow Ba6.} Bd7 12. Bd3 Bc8 $5 {Black insists on playing Ba6.} 13. Qe2 $5 {Preventing Ba6 makes sense.} (13. c4 {After this move, White has a small advantage and this is the correct idea, to play c4 and capture on d5.}) 13... Ne4 14. O-O $1 Nc6 (14... Nxc3 15. Qc2 Ne4 16. Bxe4 dxe4 17. Qxe4 Qd5 {White has the option of whether to exchange queens or not. In any case, White has a small advantage.}) 15. Rac1 Bb7 16. c4 Rc8 17. cxd5 Qxd5 18. Bc4 Qd7 19. Qd3 Nd6 20. Ng5 g6 21. Ba2 Na5 22. d5 exd5 23. Bxd5 Bxd5 24. Qxd5 Qf5 25. Qxf5 Nxf5 26. Ne4 Red8 27. g4 Nc4 28. Bb4 Nfd6 29. Nf6+ Kg7 30. Bc3 h6 31. Rfd1 Kf8 32. e4 Ke7 33. Nd5+ Kf8 34. e5 Ne4 35. Bb4+ Kg7 36. Be7 Re8 37. Bf6+ Nxf6 38. exf6+ Kf8 39. Ne7 Rc5 40. Kg2 a6 41. Rc3 Rxe7 42. fxe7+ Kxe7 43. Rcd3 h5 44. Rd7+ Ke6 45. h3 hxg4 46. hxg4 b5 47. Ra7 Rc6 48. Re1+ Kf6 49. Ree7 Nd6 50. a5 b4 51. Rec7 Rxc7 52. Rxc7 Ke5 53. Rc6 Kd5 54. Rxa6 Kc5 55. Ra8 b3 56. Rb8 Nb5 57. a6 b2 58. a7 Nxa7 59. Rxb2 Nb5 60. Kf3 Nd6 61. Kf4 Kd5 62. Re2 f6 63. g5 1-0

