1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Nc3 c6 6. Bf4 (6. Qc2 $5) (6. Bg5 $5) 6... Bd6 7. Bxd6 Qxd6 8. e3 Bf5 {The correct plan for Black.} 9. Qb3 Qe7 10. Nh4 $1 {This is a very good way for White to play in positions like this one. The early Nh4 is threatening to either exchange the bishop if it retreats to g6, or to take control of the b1-h7 diagonal.} Bg6 (10... Bc8 11. Bd3 O-O 12. O-O Ne4 13. Nf3 Nd6 14. Qc2 $14) 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. Bd3 {12.g3 is also possible, although it's not necessary that White will continue with Bg2, instead, Bd3 can still be played and later on Kf1-Kg2 for example.} O-O 13. O-O a5 14. a3 $1 {Preventing Qb4.} Na6 15. Rfe1 {White is preparing to play e3-e4 at some point.} Qd6 16. Bxa6 bxa6 17. Re2 c5 18. Rd1 c4 19. Qa4 Qb6 20. f3 Rad8 21. Qc2 Rfe8 22. Qd2 Re7 23. h3 Qc6 24. e4 dxe4 25. fxe4 Nxe4 26. d5 Qc5+ 27. Qd4 Qxd4+ 28. Rxd4 f5 29. d6 Re6 30. Nxe4 fxe4 31. Rxc4 Rdxd6 32. Rcxe4 Rxe4 33. Rxe4 Rb6 34. Re5 Rxb2 35. Rxa5 Rb6 36. Kf2 Re6 37. Kf3 Kf7 38. Kf4 Kf6 39. a4 Kf7 40. Kg5 Rc6 41. Rd5 Rc7 42. Ra5 Rc6 43. Kf4 Re6 44. Rd5 Kf6 45. a5 Rc6 46. Ke4 Ke6 47. Re5+ Kd7 48. Kd4 Rf6 49. Rg5 Kd6 50. g3 Kc6 51. h4 Rd6+ 52. Ke5 Kc5 53. Kf4+ Kd4 54. Rg4 Rf6+ 55. Kg5+ Kc5 56. Rf4 Rd6 57. Rf7 Kb4 58. Rxg7 Kxa5 59. Rxg6 Rd3 60. g4 Kb5 61. h5 a5 62. h6 Rh3 63. Rg8 a4 64. Kg6 a3 65. h7 a2 66. Ra8 1-0

